name: Peanut Butter Dog Biscuits
author: FutureChefShay
summary: A great, crunchy all-natural treat for our furry four-legged friends. If you don't have spelt flour, you can use all whole wheat.
ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat flour, or as needed
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Combine wheat flour, spelt flour, oats, and flax seeds in large bowl
Stir in water and peanut butter
Knead dough on a lightly floured surface, mixing in more flour as needed until dough is smooth and no longer sticky
Roll out dough to 1/4 inch thick
Cut with small cookie cutters into desired shapes, and place 3/4 inch apart on greased cookie sheets
Turn oven off; leave biscuits in oven until completely cool
